# AI Playtesting Guard (Manual Only)

## Critical Rule

Never launch browser tools, open localhost, navigate the game, or take screenshots
unless the user explicitly asks to playtest.

Disallowed without explicit user request:

- "Let me verify in browser"
- "Let me open the game to check"
- Any proactive browser-based validation after code edits

Allowed only when user explicitly requests playtesting with language like:

- "playtest"
- "test in browser"
- "open the game"
- "take a screenshot"
- "verify in game"

## Source of Truth for Playtesting Steps

When playtesting is explicitly requested, follow:

- `.cursor/commands/playtest.md` for full procedure and controls.

Use AI control buttons for pointer-lock transitions (do not rely on canvas click or Escape key simulation):

- `AI Enter Game` (`#ai-enter-game`)
- `AI Open Menu` (`#ai-open-menu`)
